<TEXT>
baiecomeau canada ap a soviet freighter whose cargo of 
toxic waste was turned away from britain dumped the load on this 
lawrence river seaport before dawn thursday and returned to sea 
the freighter nadezhda obukhova had returned the 15 steel 
containers of waste to canada but environmentalists in baiecomeau 
had won a court order early thursday banning the unloading of the 
polychlorinated biphenyls or pcbs it was not clear whether the 
freighters captain was aware of the court order 
lawyer shirley kennedy said several community groups she 
represents are seeking contempt charges against the captain the 
general manager of dynamis envirotech the montreal company hired to 
dispose of the cargo and a half dozen dockworkers who unloaded the 
waste 
we dont plan any action to get the ship to return to take it 
away its up to the government to get them out of here said ms 
kennedy 
joseph storozuk vice president of the ships canadian agent 
morlines said only the public utility hydroquebec and dynamis 
envirotech are named in corriveaus order 
judge paul corriveau who issued the 10day injunction against 
unloading now will consider whether to file contempt charges 
the cargo was guarded by police deployed after some residents 
rallied wednesday to protest the waste disposal plans 
dynamis envirotch lawyer laurent trudeau suggested at a court 
hearing that corriveau order the waste be stored at its intended 
destination a hydroquebec site 
polychlorinated biphenyls were used primarily as a coolant in 
electrical transformers but have been banned in north america 
because of links to cancer 
british officials say they can be safely disposed of at very high 
temperatures canada has only one such incinerator at alberta and 
it does not handle waste from other states 
when liverpool dock owners and workers refused to unload the 
cargo quebec environment minister lise bacon announced they would 
be stored at a site 20 miles from this port 
the freighter picked up the toxic waste in montreal last month 
it had been sent by truck from nearby stbasilelegrand where it 
was left over from a warehouse fire 
