five homicides per day is the norm in the big 
apple but it doesnt take a crackcrazed gunman to kill you here 
death can be as close as the nearest street corner 
ellen sauer had just decided to take a nap saturday evening when 
a steam pipe exploded beneath the street outside her manhattan 
apartment building killing her and two consolidated edison workers 
who had responded to what had been a routine call 
