pete rose and commissioner a bartlett giamatti 
reached a compromise wednesday calling for the cincinnati manager to 
be suspended indefinitely from baseball for betting on his own team 
sources said 
the exact terms of the settlement were not known but rose may 
apply for reinstatement after one year with no guarantees his 
petition will be granted sources said 
there were reports that the cincinnati manager would be out of 
baseball for as many as five years but one source said there was no 
definite length 
giamatti announced wednesday night that he would hold a news 
conference in new york at 9 am thursday however the commissioner 
did not say officially what the news conference would be about 
rose scheduled a 10 am edt news conference thursday at 
riverfront stadium rose did not address the gambling allegations 
but spoke of his new daughter cara born tuesday tyler wanted a 
baby sister so everything is going to be good rose said 
sources familiar with the case told the associated press that the 
news conference will involve roses suspension however the 
sources who spoke on condition of anonymity were not sure of the 
length of the suspension 
several baseball sources said giamatti pushed for a settlement 
because he was afraid the case would continue to linger in court 
preventing him from disciplining rose 
the sources said rose needed to settle because he believed 
giamatti ultimately would suspend him once rose exhausted legal 
appeals that need increased once baseball successfully moved the 
case into federal court 
rose under investigation since feb 20 obtained a temporary 
restraining order from an ohio state court on june 25 which 
