<TEXT>
voyager 2 discovered two more moons 
around neptune today and for the first time photographed high 
bright clouds so clearly that the clouds shadows could be seen on a 
lower layer of haze 
the two new moons bring neptunes total to eight including the 
two moons observed from earth triton and nereid and four 
previously found by voyager 
photographs returned from neptune showed dramatic and puzzling 
details in the clouds over the great dark spot an earthsized 
cyclone that is neptunes most prominent feature said bradford 
smith leader of the imaging team 
theres something about that dark spot smith said the 
clouds appear to be stationary even though the winds are moving very 
strongly through this area 
the cloud shadows voyager photographed came from similar high 
white cirruslike clouds at another spot on neptune this is the 
first time voyager has ever been able to see cloud shadows on any of 
the planets weve looked at smith said 
the positions of the shadows allowed scientists to calculate that 
the high clouds were about 30 miles above the lower layer of haze 
smith said 
as voyager 2 began its final approach to neptune it showed that 
the planets strange moon triton is a bright pink red and blue 
marble ringed by what could be a snowcovered glacier of frozen 
natural gas scientists say 
scientists also received confirmation that final instructions to 
control the spacecrafts cameras and sensors had been received said 
douglas griffith deputy mission director 
we know its in there now and were safe he said 
at 9 am pdt today voyager was 472056 miles from neptune 
caught in the grip of neptunes powerful gravity and falling toward 
the fourthlargest planet at a speed of 38599 mph 
at 856 pm pdt voyager will pass 3042 miles from neptunes 
cloud tops closer than it has come to any other celestial object on 
its 44 billionmile journey from earth 
researchers at nasas jet propulsion laboratory planned an 
allnight vigil as the most detailed images begin coming back from 
the spacecraft early friday morning it takes 4 hours and six 
minutes for radio signals from the spacecraft to reach earth 
