iranian spiritual leader put a price on his head feb 14 for the 
satanic verses which many moslems consider blasphemous 
rushdie who has since been in hiding under police guard writes 
in the threeverse 17line poem that he has chosen not to shut 
up to sing on in spite of attacks and says he has been called 
fullofhate selfaggrandizing satan selfloathing and shrill 
the poem is to appear under copyright in granta a literary 
journal edited by bill buford an american who came to cambridge 
university in 1977 as a literature student 
buford founded granta as a platform for new writing in 1979 and 
the issue containing rushdies poem celebrates the magazines 10th 
anniversary 
the poem is called 6 march 1989 which buford said was the 
date it was written 20 days after khomeinis ruling 
buford said rushdie was among writers who contributed to the 
first issue and were invited to publish new work in the anniversary 
edition 
that invitation went out before khomeinis death sentence and 
rushdie had been expected to contribute a prose piece buford said 
but instead a typewritten poem arrived with no accompanying 
explanation of any sort 
buford who provided a copy of the poem said he had verified 
that it was indeed rushdies work 
i think it is an important heartfelt statement of a man 
feeling alone and isolated and estranged from friends public and 
audience who is under circumstances that no writer in living memory 
has had to live under buford told the associated press 
i think its moving and in its way quite profound he said 
rushdie remains in hiding with his wife novelist marianne 
wiggins khomeini died in june but the death sentence was not 
lifted and the indianborn moslem writer has published nothing 
except a brief apology for any offense caused to moslems and a few 
book reviews in the weekly observer newspaper 
