<TEXT>
a distinct identity for chevrolets geo line of 
small vehicles still hasnt been developed nearly a year after the 
first of the cars were introduced a company executive says 
chevrolet general manager jim perkins said wednesday the gm 
division is about halfway through its process of developing its geo 
franchise 
the company is walking a narrow path between selling and 
servicing the three geo cars and one truck at chevrolet dealers and 
fostering a separate image for the nameplate 
geo cars were introduced in january since then one model the 
spectrum has been dropped and two the metro and storm have been 
added 
separate geo signs are going up at dealerships and some chevrolet 
dealers are taking out space in commercial telephone books in the 
gs to encourage the brand distinction 
also chevrolets wellknown heartbeat of america advertising 
theme going into its fourth year will not be used in geo ads 
instead those ads feature the theme getting to know geo to 
the tune of getting to know you from the play the king and 
i 
the geo imagery is going to become more focused than it has 
been in the past perkins said 
perkins speaking during the introduction of the chevrolet lineup 
for 1990 also said gm is ready to give chevrolet dealers a hand in 
marketing the geo and will boost the potential dealer profit margin 
on geo cars and trucks 
