<TEXT>
holiday corp announced the end of its 
reign as americas innkeeper thursday with an agreement to sell 
the holiday inn chain to britains brewing giant bass plc for 223 
billion 
holiday corp said it would form a new subsidiary to run its 
profitable casino business and newer hotel brands embassy suites 
hampton inn and homewood suites 
the announcement was welcomed by investors in the company well 
known for the hundreds of holiday inns that dot the nations 
highways and cities there had been rampant speculation that holiday 
corp would be vulnerable to an unwanted takeover without some sort 
of major restructuring 
holiday corp stock surged 6 a share to 83 in heavy new york 
stock exchange trading on the news 
it clearly focuses holiday corp in the highgrowth segments 
of the hotel business and makes it a more clearly focused company 
said marvin roffman a market analyst with janney montogmery scott 
inc of philadelphia 
the announcement also marked the end of holiday corps leading 
position as owner of the dominant hotel chain in the country a 
status that led the company to describe itself as americas 
innkeeper 
michael d rose holiday corps chief executive officer said 
the companys newer hotel brands have grown to the point they 
compete with holiday inn in the marketplace and for attention within 
the corporation 
it became increasingly clear to us that a separation of holiday 
inns from holiday corps other brands was the most effective 
positioning of the brands in the 1990s and beyond rose said in a 
statement 
the sale which requires shareholder approval calls for holiday 
corps stockholders to draw onequarter share of bass stock for 
each holiday corp share with a value calculated at 125 million 
bass also will assume about 21 billion in outstanding holiday 
debt making the deal worth 23 billion 
in addition the spunoff company will pay a special 35ashare 
cash dividend to holiday corp shareholders worth nearly 935 
million holiday corp has 267 million shares outstanding 
the sale to bass will allow holiday corp to retire 21 billion 
in outstanding debt much of which stems from the companys 
financial recapitalization in 1987 holiday spokesman ralph berry 
said 
as a result of that the new company when its spun off will be 
virtually debt free it will then borrow or finance new borrowing to 
pay the dividend he said 
in addition to approval from shareholders of both companies the 
agreement must also be sanctioned by nevada and new jersey gaming 
officials 
with the sale bass will acquire 55 owned or leased properties as 
well as franchise agreements joint venture agreements and 
management contracts covering 1400 holiday inn hotels in north 
america 
last year bass bought the rights to franchise holiday inn hotels 
outside north america as the result of that and other purchases it 
already owns 14 holiday inn hotels in the southeast united states 
and is a major franchisee in canada 
bass has more than 7300 pubs and other food and drink outlets in 
the united kingdom the company also brews bass carling black label 
and other beers and has annual sales approaching 6 billion 
holiday has sold off numerous assets in recent years as the 
company directed its energies toward property management rather than 
ownership the company sold 127 hotels between 1985 and last year 
berry said 
that was merely selling property but retaining management of 
those properties where this is actually a transaction that will 
remove us from the holiday inns business he said 
bass is expected to keep holiday inns north american 
headquarters in memphis berry said and holiday corp employees now 
working for holiday inn will become bass employees 
roffman said holiday corp is wise to concentrate on its newer 
hotel brands and casinohotel company harrahs 
harrahs is one of the leaders in the gaming industry with 
highly profitable properties roffman said the company is 
poised for substantial growth in their new form and with a much 
better balance sheet 
