the pension fund covering most of the nations 
college faculty members will have more investment options to offer 
participants under a settlement approved thursday by the securities 
and exchange commission 
the sec approved an agreement reached in december among 
teachers insurance and annuity association of america and college 
retirement equities fund and several academic and investment groups 
under the settlement tiaacref policyholders before they 
retire will be able to transfer their funds to other investments 
or take a lump sum payment in cash of their accumulated funds both 
alternatives are subject to employer approval 
tiaacref is one of the nations largest pension funds with 
investments of more than 60 billion on behalf of professors and 
other employees of colleges and nonprofit groups 
the other signatories to the agreement are the american council 
on education the american association of university professors the 
investment company institute a national association of 2700 mutual 
funds the national education association stanford university 
united university professions and four mutual fund complexes 
a mutual fund is an investment company that pools money from 
shareholders and invests it in a variety of securities including 
stocks bonds and money market securities 
some professors had been quarreling with the nonprofit pension 
fund in recent years over its investment rules and policies 
especially in the wake of the 1987 stock market crash 
tiaacref had sought exemptions from the investment company act 
of 1940 one of the laws enforced by the sec to allow it to 
restrict how and when it would redeem or buy back policyholders 
